Key Match Events: Ben Stokes and Chris Woakes combined for an England-record stand to rescue their team from 192 for 6 to 339 for 9
Ben Stokes scored 108 runs off 84 balls and was awarded the Player of the Match award
Pre-Game Insights: England captain Jos Buttler said they were desperate for the win and thought 339 was a good score
Netherlands captain Scott Edwards said they had a few recurring issues to address to win their last game and get a better shot at making the Champions Trophy
Post-Match Reflections: Jos Buttler said they were delighted with Ben Stokes' performance and thought he took charge of the game at the right time
Scott Edwards said they were disappointed with their performance and would talk about it to figure out what to do better
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at the Maharashtra Cricket Association Stadium in Pune, with a crowd of 9,217 in attendance
England's win snapped their five-game losing streak
The Netherlands' loss means they have a few recurring issues to address to win their last game and get a better shot at making the Champions Trophy
